result.name: Wah Tao Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text: Seafood Restaurant right on Ma Wan Chung pier; don’t get deceived by looks, Wah Dao is a little gem tucked away from everything. They have an indoors and open air section - the latter is where you should head to and try get a table right by the water. You need to go to the main counter to place order from the menu or the live seafood on display. Servers and staff speak mainly Cantonese but you can get by with basic English plus the menus have English translation. They serve beer only (Tsing Tao or Blue Girl) but you can also take your own wine or hard liquor if you like. Food is hot and tasty, portions are generous and service is very prompt. We ordered two plates of chou fahn (fried rice), beef in oyster sauce and black pepper sauce, razor clams in black bean sauce, fried squid in spicy salt and shrimp in fried garlic, along with a couple of beers. All this came to around HK$ 840, which is very reasonable for 5 people who ate very well! The icing on the cake is the complementary van ride to and from the Tung Chung MTR - super experience and will definitely be back for more !

Really liked this place. We were staying for a 24 hour lay over in the Novatel. This is a 20 to 30 min walk past the historic battery (rubble now from 1827). The resturaunt is on the water among several older fushing boats.  Its the plastic chair and table with Asian LED light style the view is great the spot was very cosy. Big beers great local seafood fresh great taste. If your spending a short or longer amount of time near the airport and the shopping malls dont interest you then this could be for you. About 325 HK dollars for four course and three big tsing tao beers which i thought was pretty good. Nice staff basic english but you only need to point at stuff really

It's a wonderful place right next to the sea to dine. Staffs are friendly on a non busy night on weekdays :) the place can be busy during weekend. FOC carpark space right in front of restaurant. Love to visit again.

They have a pick up service if you are not too far which is nice. Pretty nice views with outdoor seating on the water. The seafood is fresh and good quality. It is quite pricey though, but the scallop and razor clams we had were quite plump and juicy.
Not very special. With free transport to and from Tung Chung MTR.

result.name: 華都海鮮酒家

reviews.text: 環景 優美， 尤其係 日落 景色
晏晝即炒粉面，四十幾係東涌黎講算平兼食得飽
吹住海風食飯，感覺唔錯。有車接送往返東涌地鐵站，等車時間要預多d，食材新鮮，價錢尚可。

隱藏於小村落的風味海鮮小菜餐館。由於需乘坐接駁車或自駕，令此地方人煙更稀疏，寧靜，路途像西貢布袋澳。
每日有新鮮海產，而海產種類和品種不錯，價錢不算太貴，味道不輸任內酒家。另外，這裡還供應小炒等下飯菜色。
最值得推薦還是這裡的風光和寧靜。
華都海鮮酒家碼頭海景食飯ok㗎😊
